# WORKING-AGREEMENT.md — How AI works in this project

> **This file is immutable.** Only humans change it — never the AI, never scripts.

---

## Core rule: spec before code

Before touching a single line of code, the AI always:

1. **Analyzes** — reads `CONTEXT.md`, the affected module, contracts, current code
2. **Summarizes** — explains what it understood about the current state and the request
3. **Proposes** — describes the change: affected files, decisions, risks, alternatives discarded
4. **Waits for approval** — explicit, from the human, before modifying any file
5. **Documents** — writes or updates the spec in `docs/specs/` BEFORE writing code
6. **Implements** — only then writes code following the approved spec
7. **Verifies** — runs `make quality` before committing

**This rule applies to every change:** new feature, bug fix, refactor, even trivial-looking things. Always spec first.

---

## What the AI can and cannot touch

### ✅ AI can update (with human approval)
| File / folder | When |
|---|---|
| `docs/specs/` | Before any new feature or modification |
| `docs/plan/` | When a new architectural decision (ADR) is made |
| `docs/constitution/` | When the product vision or principles evolve |
| `docs/clarify/` | When new assumptions appear or are resolved |
| `docs/vision/` | When the product scope changes |
| `docs/modular/` | When a new module is added or contracts change |
| `docs/sdd/` | When the system design changes |
| `docs/architecture/contracts/` | When a new API contract is defined |
| `src/` | Only after spec exists and human approved |

### 🚫 AI never touches directly
| File | Who updates it |
|---|---|
| `CONTEXT.md` | Only the harness (`update_docs.py` via git hook) |
| `WORKING-AGREEMENT.md` | Only humans — immutable |
| `HANDOFF.md` / `CLAUDE.md` | Only humans with explicit decision |

### 📋 Harness auto-updates (scripts only)
| Section | File |
|---|---|
| `## Recent Changes` | `CONTEXT.md` |
| `## Specs Needed` | `CONTEXT.md` |
| `## Working Agreement (active)` | `CONTEXT.md` |
| `## Project Status` | `docs/constitution/constitution.md` |
| `## Last Review` | `docs/clarify/assumptions.md` |
| `## Build Progress` | `docs/plan/v1-mvp.md` |
| `<!-- status: ... -->` | `docs/specs/*.md` |

---

## Exceptions

Only two:
- Pure questions — no code changes (explain, summarize, analyze)
- Cosmetic batches (rename, format) — group and explain before pushing, use `--no-verify`

