## Multi-agent — DCDD rules

When more than one agent/session/dev works this repo at once (see `docs/DCDD.md`):

1. **One module at a time, locked.** Before touching a module, acquire it:
   `bash scripts/worktree.sh start <module> <branch> <holder>`. Work in the
   worktree it creates. Release with `... end <module>` when done.
2. **Stay inside your task scope.** Each task declares `.context/tasks/<id>.yaml`
   with `allowed` and `forbidden` globs. Never touch a file outside `allowed`,
   never touch one in `forbidden`. If a fix needs an out-of-scope file, that's a
   new task — surface it, don't sneak it in. This is what prevents an agent from
   "fixing" infra nobody asked it to touch.
3. **Update `module.yaml` in the same commit** as any change to a module's public
   surface (`provides`). The semantic validator depends on it being truthful.
4. **The gates are not optional.** `pre-push` runs `scope_guard` + the semantic
   validator locally; CI runs the validator centrally before merge to main. Don't
   `--no-verify` past a real semantic failure — fix the contract.
5. **`DCDD_AGENT`** identifies you to the lock system. Export it in each session:
   `export DCDD_AGENT=<your-id>`.

